payload.text:
**Summarizing code review findings**

I'll note the key issues: invalid HTML in patient-dashboard causing layout and script problems, untranslated placeholder text in carb.html, potential navigation problems from inconsistent data-nav usage, and some script loading and translation omissions. Then I‚Äôll provide a clear bullet list highlighting these points with recommendations for fixes.

payload.message:
- `frontend/patient/patient-dashboard.html:62-69` the `section.pd-content` tag never closes before `</main>`. That leaves an unclosed section and puts the footer inside the main element in the parsed DOM. Close `</section>` and then `</main>` to restore valid layout and avoid script/CSS targeting issues.
- `frontend/patient/carb.html:48` shows the raw key `carb.subtitle` instead of a readable subtitle. Provide an actual localized string (or add the missing translation entry) so users don‚Äôt see the placeholder.
- `frontend/patient/appointments.html:51-53` the sidebar entries for Labs/Carb/Maps are plain `<li>` elements without navigation (no `onclick`/link like the others). They won‚Äôt navigate anywhere unless additional JS handles them; if you expect them to be clickable, wire them up consistently.

The Mongoose model in `backend/models/Prescription.js` looks structurally fine for basic CRUD.

If you want, I can patch the missing closing tag and text fixes.

- `frontend/patient/patient-dashboard.html:62-69` the `section.pd-content` tag never closes before `</main>`. That leaves an unclosed section and puts the footer inside the main element in the parsed DOM. Close `</section>` and then `</main>` to restore valid layout and avoid script/CSS targeting issues.
- `frontend/patient/carb.html:48` shows the raw key `carb.subtitle` instead of a readable subtitle. Provide an actual localized string (or add the missing translation entry) so users don‚Äôt see the placeholder.
- `frontend/patient/appointments.html:51-53` the sidebar entries for Labs/Carb/Maps are plain `<li>` elements without navigation (no `onclick`/link like the others). They won‚Äôt navigate anywhere unless additional JS handles them; if you expect them to be clickable, wire them up consistently.

The Mongoose model in `backend/models/Prescription.js` looks structurally fine for basic CRUD.

If you want, I can patch the missing closing tag and text fixes.
